seed_chunks:
Rain-polished streets belong, on paper, to the **Harbor Union Council**, which claims it’s only keeping men fed and contracts fair; in back rooms it runs “protection” routes for bodies and evidence, selling silence to the highest bidder. The **Civic Virtue League** parades as a charity for widows and wayward youth, but it launders blackmail through soup lines and steers missing persons into “rehabilitation” that never ends. Over both leans **Veylan Foundry & Shipping**, a respectable industrial house funding jobs and philanthropy while field-testing a private registry of workers—disappearances as data. The Union extorts Veylan, Veylan bankrolls the League, and the League breaks strikers—each blaming the others when someone vanishes.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "Harbor Union Council",
      "public_front": "Labor organization protecting wages, safety, and fair contracts on the docks and in the mills.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Controls illicit transport corridors for people, evidence, and hush money; brokers disappearances as a service."
    },
    {
      "name": "Civic Virtue League",
      "public_front": "Prominent charity offering shelters, soup lines, and moral reform programs for the poor.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Runs a blackmail-and-recruitment pipeline using aid records; funnels select 'cases' into permanent off-book custody."
    },
    {
      "name": "Veylan Foundry & Shipping",
      "public_front": "Major employer and benefactor providing industrial growth, shipping infrastructure, and civic donations.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Operates a covert registry and experimentation program treating workers and missing persons as controllable inventory."
    }
  ]
}
```

Dockside sirens wail as the Harbor Union Council calls an “emergency safety stoppage” after a crate-manifest clerk is found drowned in a dry warehouse—his ledger gone, his pockets stuffed with Civic Virtue League ration chits. The League responds by expanding night “curfew escorts” for soup-line regulars, and three youths vanish between the chapel and the trolley stop. Meanwhile Veylan Foundry & Shipping rushes a sealed midnight shipment through Pier Nine under private guards, bribing union stewards to look away. Rumor says the cargo is people, not parts, and someone’s selling names.

```json
{
  "events": [
    {
      "name": "The Dry-Drown Ledger",
      "description": "A Harbor Union Council manifest clerk is found drowned in a warehouse with no standing water; his ledger is missing and Civic Virtue League ration chits are planted on him. The Union declares an emergency stoppage and starts shaking down dockworkers for “answers.”",
      "tensions": [
        "Work stoppage turns the docks volatile; anyone asking questions risks being labeled a scab or a snitch.",
        "The missing ledger could expose protection routes for bodies/evidence, making its holder a target for all three factions.",
        "Planted League chits threaten to spark street retaliation against soup-line patrons and shelter staff."
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Pier Nine Midnight Run",
      "description": "Veylan Foundry & Shipping pushes a sealed late-night convoy through Pier Nine under private guards, paying off select union stewards to clear the gates. The Civic Virtue League expands ‘curfew escorts’ that coincide with three youths vanishing en route from the chapel to the trolley stop.",
      "tensions": [
        "Union stewards taking bribes risk exposure; whistleblowers may disappear before dawn.",
        "The League’s escorts create a legal-looking abduction corridor that can swallow witnesses and runaways.",
        "If the shipment is human cargo, any investigation threatens to trigger a coordinated cover-up across Union, League, and Veylan security."
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

